

ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Remove old Docker (if any)
sudo apt remove -y docker docker.io containerd runc

ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Install prerequisites
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg

ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Add Dockerâ€™s official GPG key
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg

ðŸ”¹ Step 4: Add Docker repository (IMPORTANT)
echo \
"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] \
https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
$(. /etc/os-release && echo "$VERSION_CODENAME") stable" | \
sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null


For you, VERSION_CODENAME = noble.

ðŸ”¹ Step 5: Install Docker + Compose plugin
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

ðŸ”¹ Step 6: Verify
docker --version
docker compose version


âœ… You should see:

Docker version 26.x.x
Docker Compose version v2.x.x

ðŸ”¹ Step 7 (Optional but recommended): Run Docker without sudo
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker


Test:

